# No Manual Production Commits

Never commit and push to `main` manually (via `git add`, `git commit`, `git push`) when the intent is a production deploy.

Use the appropriate deploy script instead:

- **Backend changes** -- `Update-Prod-App-Backend.ps1` (auto-bumps version in `backend/VERSION`, commits, pushes, tags, and deploys to EC2 via SSM)
- **Electron/client changes** -- `Update-Prod-App-Electron.ps1` (auto-bumps version, commits, pushes, tags, and builds the installer)

Both scripts handle version bumping, tagging, and deployment in one atomic flow. Manual commits bypass version tracking and can desync the tag history.

If only the SSM deploy step is needed (code already committed and pushed), pass `-SkipCommit -SkipPush` to the backend script.
